                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origPlace/>
                            <origDate notBefore="1872" notAfter="1889" cert="medium"/>
                            <note>
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">King Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> (f.6),
                            Coptic Patriach Peter and
                            Ethiopian <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8388SalamaI">Metropolitan Salāmā III</persName>,
                             are mentioned in the prayers (for instance, f. 19v).
                            The catalogue identifies Peter as the Coptic Patriarch
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11721PeterVIIAlex">Peter VII of Alexandria</persName> but this is uncertain since
                            he died in <date>1852</date>, before the ascension of Yoḥannǝs IV on the throne in 1872.
                            Metropolitan Salāmā III
                          died also before that date, in 1867.</note>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>. The name of the original owner, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12632HaylaMikael">Ḫāyla Mikaʾel</persName>,
                            appears on f. 19, is half erased. <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12634MenetaSedeq">ʾAbuna Mǝneta Ṣādǝq</persName> is mentioned on ff. 43v, 52v etc.
                            Collected by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7674Orlov">Alexander Orlov</persName> in Ethiopia.</provenance>
                          <acquisition>The manuscript was acquired by
                            the Asiatic Museum on <date>10 September 1903</date>.</acquisition>

                    </history>
